  <p>Specifying an invalid location for either <pf>.insert()</pf> or <pf>.erase()</pf> will result in an exception being thrown. You can test this out in the sample above by specifying something like <pf>letters.begin() + 100</pf> for one of the locations.</p>

  <exercise label="vectors_insertion-removal-ex-1">
    <statement>
      <p>Given this sequence of operations, what would <pf>nums</pf> contain?</p>
      <program><![CDATA[ 
vector<int> nums;
nums.push_back(8);
nums.push_back(3);
values.pop_back();
nums.push_back(5);
nums.push_back(4);
values.pop_back();
nums.push_back(9);
      ]]>
      </program>
    </statement>
    <choices randomize="yes">
      <choice correct="yes">
        <statement>
          <pf>8 5 9</pf>
        </statement>
      </choice>
      <choice>
        <statement>
          <pf>9 5 8</pf>
        </statement>
      </choice>
      <choice>
        <statement>
          <pf>3 5 9</pf>
        </statement>
      </choice>
      <choice>
        <statement>
          <pf>9 3 5</pf>
        </statement>
      </choice>
    </choices>
  </exercise>

